The article discusses President Barack Obama's praise for the restoration of the Pay-As-You-Go rule, which requires Congress to cover the cost of expenses at the time they are incurred. The President emphasizes the need for fiscal responsibility and calls on both parties to put aside politics and address the deficit. He plans to create a Fiscal Commission through executive order to achieve this goal. The President highlights the importance of the Pay-As-You-Go rule in maintaining budget balance and blames its abandonment for the massive deficits in recent years. He acknowledges the challenges of responsible budgeting in Washington but expresses satisfaction that the law has been restored. The President also proposes other measures, including spending cuts and a freeze on government expenses, to address the deficit. He emphasizes the need for bipartisan cooperation and tough decision-making to solve the fiscal problem.